You are hungry! Let's cook a delicious meal. Check the cookbook in the kitchen for the recipe. Once done, enjoy your meal!

-= Kitchen =-
You are in a kitchen. An ordinary one. You begin to take stock of what's here.

You can see a fridge. You can't wait to tell the folks at home about this! The fridge contains a carrot. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. You can see a table. The table is massive. On the table you make out a cookbook and a knife. Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's a counter. Now why would someone leave that there? The counter is vast. But oh no! there's nothing on this piece of garbage. You can make out a stove. The stove is conventional. But the thing hasn't got anything on it.
